5:["$","$L10",null,{"children":[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"Article\",\"headline\":\"Best DJ Mixers for Vinyl in 2025: From Club Standard to Budget Picks\",\"description\":\"Looking for the best DJ mixer for vinyl? We cover the top mixers in 2025 — from the Allen & Heath Xone:92 to budget-friendly options — with honest recommendations for every level.\",\"datePublished\":\"March 30, 2025\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"45 Mix Trackr\",\"url\":\"https://www.45mixtrackr.com\"},\"publisher\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"45 Mix Trackr\",\"url\":\"https://www.45mixtrackr.com\"},\"mainEntityOfPage\":{\"@type\":\"WebPage\",\"@id\":\"https://www.45mixtrackr.com/blog/best-dj-mixers-for-vinyl\"}}"}}],["$","article",null,{"className":"max-w-2xl text-white","children":[["$","$L11",null,{"href":"/blog","className":"inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-[#B3B3B3] hover:text-white text-sm mb-8 transition-colors","children":[["$","svg",null,{"className":"w-4 h-4","fill":"currentColor","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","children":["$","path",null,{"d":"M15.41 16.59L10.83 12l4.58-4.59L14 6l-6 6 6 6z"}]}],"All posts"]}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-black leading-tight mb-3","children":"Best DJ Mixers for Vinyl in 2025: From Club Standard to Budget Picks"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 text-xs text-[#6B6B6B] mb-10","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":"March 30, 2025"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"•"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"7 min read"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h2","0",{"className":"text-white text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4","children":"Introduction"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"The mixer is the heart of any vinyl DJ setup. It sits between your turntables, blends the audio, shapes the EQ, and determines how much control you have over your mix. Unlike CDJs or controllers, a great analog mixer lasts decades — some DJs still use the same unit they bought in the 1990s."}}],["$","p","2",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"This guide covers the best DJ mixers for vinyl across every price point, with honest assessments of what each one offers."}}],["$","hr","3",{"className":"border-[#282828] my-8"}],["$","h2","4",{"className":"text-white text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4","children":"What Makes a Good Vinyl DJ Mixer?"}],["$","p","5",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Before buying, understand what matters for vinyl specifically:"}}],["$","p","6",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"<strong class=\"text-white\">Phono preamps</strong> — Vinyl produces a low-level phono signal that must be amplified. Every mixer on this list has phono inputs, but their quality varies significantly. Better phono preamps mean lower noise and more accurate EQ."}}],["$","p","7",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"<strong class=\"text-white\">EQ section</strong> — Vinyl DJs rely heavily on the EQ to blend tracks. Three-band EQ (low, mid, high) is standard, but some mixers offer kill switches per band — vital for mixing technique."}}],["$","p","8",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"<strong class=\"text-white\">Channel faders</strong> — Smooth, consistent faders are critical. Cheap faders develop scratchy, inconsistent travel over time."}}],["$","p","9",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"<strong class=\"text-white\">Build quality</strong> — A mixer that lives in a club gets handled roughly. Metal chassis and quality crossfader mechanisms matter."}}],"$L12","$L13","$L14","$L15","$L16","$L17","$L18","$L19","$L1a","$L1b","$L1c","$L1d","$L1e","$L1f","$L20","$L21","$L22","$L23","$L24","$L25","$L26","$L27","$L28","$L29","$L2a","$L2b","$L2c","$L2d","$L2e","$L2f","$L30","$L31","$L32","$L33","$L34","$L35","$L36","$L37","$L38","$L39","$L3a"]}],"$L3b","$L3c"]}]]}]
